POLICE have arrested two suspects linked to a business burglary where 11 firearms and ammunition were stolen. The suspects, aged 32 and 36, were arrested in White City, Mpumalanga, and Hoedspruit in Limpopo during a weekend operation. Cops received information about the whereabouts of one of the suspects who allegedly committed the burglary in March 2021, and rushed to the place in Mpumalanga on Friday, 13 January. They found the suspect and during a search of the house, police found firearms and ammunition. Limpopo police spokesman Colonel Malesela Ledwaba said the 32-year-old and his accomplice were arrested.  suspect was arrested as he could not explain where the items came from. The police arrested the 32-year-old male suspect at a farm in Hoedspruit. “The suspect, a resident at Eslington Mhala policing area was found with a firearm and he was also placed under arrest,” said Ledwaba. He said the suspects were arrested by the members of the Phalaborwa Crime Intelligence, Hoedspruit detectives, Mopani District task team and Limpopo Highway Patrol following a business burglary in March 2021 after 11 firearms and ammunition were stolen in Hoedspruit. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  The suspects are expected to appear in the Hoedspruit Magistrates Court soon facing charges of business burglary and possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. “Police investigations are continuing,” Ledwaba told Daily Sun.